Hey Jude (original title: The Beatles Again) is a 1970 collection of non-album singles and B-sides by the Beatles. It included "I Should Have Known Better" and "Can't Buy Me Love", two singles released by Capitol Records whose only previous American album appearance had been on the A Hard Day's Night soundtrack album which had been released by United Artists Records. The album had been out of print since the late 1980s, but was officially re-released for the first time on CD individually and in a boxed set entitled The U.S. Albums in 2014.
